data.title: Iron Man of Laos
data.meta_description: Iron Man of Laos - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document provides an overview of the Southeast Asia Program at Cornell University, which was established in 1950. It is an interdisciplinary program focused on the study of Southeast Asia and its individual countries. The program offers undergraduate and graduate courses taught by specialists in Southeast Asian culture and current affairs. It also sponsors research projects on various Southeast Asian countries and languages. Students and faculty conduct field research throughout Southeast Asia. The program publishes works related to Southeast Asia and provides information on courses, fellowships, and degree requirements.
